B.NO=s(["Starting a SIP of just \u20b9500/month at age 15 can make you a crorepati by retirement! \ud83c\udf89","The Rule of 72: divide 72 by your annual interest rate to find how many years it takes to double your money. At 8%, that's just 9 years! \ud83d\udcc8","An FD of \u20b91 lakh at 7% interest compounded yearly grows to over \u20b91.97 lakh in 10 years \u2014 without you lifting a finger! \ud83c\udfe6","Paying even \u20b9500 extra on your home loan EMI every month can cut years off your loan tenure and save lakhs in interest! \ud83c\udfe0","Starting to invest just 5 years earlier can nearly double your final corpus thanks to the magic of compounding. Time is your biggest asset! \u23f3","A Recurring Deposit (RD) is a great first investment for beginners \u2014 you save a fixed amount every month and earn guaranteed interest! \ud83d\udcb0","India's inflation averages around 5\u20136% per year. If your money isn't growing faster than that, you're actually losing purchasing power! \ud83d\udcc9",'SIP investments benefit from "Rupee Cost Averaging" \u2014 you buy more units when markets are low and fewer when high, reducing your average cost! \ud83d\udd04',"Home loan interest rates in India are often linked to the RBI repo rate. When RBI cuts rates, your EMI can actually go down! \ud83c\udfdb\ufe0f","Even a 0.5% lower interest rate on a \u20b930 lakh home loan can save you over \u20b91 lakh across the loan tenure. Always compare lenders! \ud83d\udd0d","The longer your SIP tenure, the more powerful compounding becomes. A 20-year SIP can grow 3\xd7 more than a 10-year SIP with the same monthly amount! \ud83d\ude80","Fixed Deposits are covered under DICGC insurance up to \u20b95 lakh per bank. Your savings are protected even if the bank faces trouble! \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f","Missing even 2\u20133 SIP payments a year can significantly reduce your final returns. Set up auto-debit to stay consistent! \ud83e\udd16","A personal loan typically has much higher interest (12\u201324%) compared to a home loan (8\u201310%). Always prefer secured loans when possible! \u26a0\ufe0f","In a step-up SIP, you increase your investment amount by 10% every year. This small habit can double your final wealth compared to a flat SIP! \ud83d\udcca","Pre-paying your home loan in the first few years is most effective \u2014 that's when the interest component of your EMI is the highest! \ud83d\udca1","\u20b910,000/month in SIP at 12% returns for 25 years grows to over \u20b91.9 crore. The secret? Starting early and staying invested! \ud83c\udf31","Tax-saving FDs have a 5-year lock-in but let you claim deductions up to \u20b91.5 lakh under Section 80C. A safe way to save tax! \ud83e\uddfe","The interest you earn on an RD is taxable, but the principal is not. Always account for tax when comparing RD vs FD returns! \ud83d\udccb","Compound interest works best with time \u2014 even a single extra year of investment can add thousands to your final maturity amount! \u2728"],t.s)
